#####################################
# 
# Start webserver
#

To start the webservice from source
  1. Change into the subi directory 
     e.g. cd subi

  2. Launch the webserver
     sudo python subi.py
  
  3. Visit localhost
     http://localhost/index.html

####################################
# 
# Build applications
#

To build a mac or windows application

  1. Start in subi directory
     e.g. cd subi/
  
  2. Remove previous build lines
     rm -rf build dist/
  
  3. Build the app
     python setup.py py2app     # Add -A option to use source files (for updating)
  
  4. Kill any exisiting webservers 
     ps -a                      (find the process id of the webserver)
     e.g. sudo kill -9 24234    (if the process id was 24234)
  
  5. Launch the app
     sudo ./dist/subi.app/Contents/MacOS/subi


To edit setup.py

  Setup.py code was borrowed from 
  http://svn.pythonmac.org/py2app/py2app/trunk/doc/index.html#self-bootstrapping
  It is made to setup both windows and mac.
  There are many options that can be changed.
  Just be sure to avoid the option ARGV
  which kill mac
